description.narrative: The project Oxfam Novib Incubation offers technical assistance and capacity building services to start ups and young social enterprises (micro-enterprises and SMEs) in our three focus countries; Vietnam, Nigeria and Uganda (think of market studies, business strategy development, building winning teams, provide convertible seed capital). Business incubation support offers entrepreneurs coaching and limited financial support to help develop sound business plans. Our business development team works with local incubator organizations in order to enable training and tailor-made business support. We want to ensure that brilliant ideas also translate into investable business plans, by focusing on entrepreneurs who are capable of moving quickly from creating business ideas to being investment ready.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib is one of the 17 national affiliates of the Oxfam International Confederation. It started life in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Working together in confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education forall, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novibs main office is based in The Netherlands, itsupports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fund raising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s head office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
